title: Webpack

title: ESLint
description: ESLint is an open source JavaScript linting utility originally created by Nicholas C. Zakas in June 2013. Code linting is a type of static analysis that is frequently used to find problematic patterns or code that doesn't adhere to certain style guidelines.

title: Axios
description: Axios is a Javascript library used to make HTTP requests from node.js or XMLHttpRequests

title: Babel
description: Babel is a toolchain that is mainly used to convert ECMAScript 2015+ code into a backwards compatible version of JavaScript in current and older browsers
